(my two cents) Thank you. I have to admit I was a little put off when I heard you doing that, it seemed very controlling- first of all because someone from this site rewrote the page, or reversed the order and then secondly now that the article represents us on a very popular site for one person to change that without having a discussion.

Very overeager, in my opinion. We don't have to jump on the mention or create some kind of, in my opinion, lame connection or reference in the form of a joke SCP. If it is to be done, it should be written up like a data breach file or groups of interest report. (the new revision is a good example of how it should be done) Nothing has to be put up now however. Lets just give it some time. Maybe eventually we can all agree on some cool fun protocol,(or do nothing, but if has to be one or the other, we can't just have random people doing whatever) were we write the site up and then visit, register accounts, and pretend to be agents, telling them to delete it immediately, or spam it with threatening phrases like, "this information is confidential, all posters names and addresses have been taken down" and "delete immediately" and then bombard them with creepy meme pictures. Where anyone who has duel accounts anywhere would be put on a double agent list/ a list of the names of suspected leaks. Maybe even where to get on the forums requires a password, so everything looks real. That would be original. That would have some mystique and get people talking.

We're no where near that popular though. I mean right now half the people writing the tv tropes page have accounts here, and then to link them up, to "synchronize" them..gah…let some other non biased troppers have at it first.





